	     Durban – A shootout between a civilian and armed robbers at the Pavilion Shopping Mall in Durban has left one person injured.  "We can confirm a shooting took place at the parking lot of a mall in Durban. It appears the suspects tried to rob someone at the parking.  "A civilian shot at the suspects and the suspects retaliated. As a result, another civilian was shot and wounded," police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane told News24 shortly after the incident occurred.  Zwane said the suspects had fled the scene. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  